{
  "stem": "935.7",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The other thing I learned is that [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] right there and then, you sit down, you don't get up anymore.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Perhaps you get up this day, or the next, but altogether, it means you're giving up.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You're giving in, you're giving up.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, there's no guarantee that if you don't get up, I mean, if you stand, that you're going to make it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But these are signs, right in the beginning, where you make a conscious or subconscious decision to fight at all.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It doesn't matter what happens.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So then you do the best you can.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that's when I saw also-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] while all this was going on, and the SS guards were throwing those little bowls after them, I saw one young Greek woman, naked, sitting against one of those barracks, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] giggling to herself, and looking around sheepishly, drinking her own milk.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A young mother.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She had killed her baby herself, her newborn baby, before they could kill it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And now, she had, of course, gone mad, like most people were in there, including the guards.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And now she drank her own milk, and looked around like this, giggling very happily, thinking that nobody should steal that milk from her.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that's when you know you're not-- you are in something which can never be described, because the worst insanity asylum is sane compared to that.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Guards were drunk all the time.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Guards couldn't count, which means you had to stand for hours, and hours, and hours, because they were too stupid to count.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They played Russian roulette there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Not with a gun, it would've been too simple.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They lined you up for the famous appell, to be counted.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
